'''Marvin Doecadez Sonsona''' (born July 25, 1990) is a Filipino [[professional boxer]] and former [[WBO]] [[super flyweight]] champion. A relative of his named [[Eden Sonsona]] is also a boxer and a former Philippine national bantamweight champion.<ref>{{cite news
| author = Abac Cordero
| title = Sonsona's wish: Good life for family
| publisher = The Philippine Star
| page = 12
| date = September 8, 2009
| accessdate = 2009-09-08
 }}</ref> One of Sonsona's trainers is Nonito Donaire Sr., father and trainer of [[Nonito Donaire]].<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/?m=show&id=22046
|title=Sonsona vs Donaire? The Pinoy Mayweathers?
|date=September 7, 2009
|accessdate=2009-09-08
|author=Rick Reeno
|publisher=BoxingScene.com
}}</ref>

==Professional career==
Sonsona started boxing at seven years of age under the tutelage of his uncle. Before fighting as a professional, he fought 150 times as an [[amateur boxing|amateur]].<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://philboxing.com/news/story-21073.html
|title=MARVELOUS MARVIN SONSONA RETURNS TO ACTION TOMORROW IN 'TRIPLE THRILLA'
|date=December 12, 2008
|accessdate=2009-09-07
|publisher=PhilBoxing.com
}}</ref>

He won his professional debut on points then knocked out his next ten opponents in short rounds. All his first opponents were unknowns but then he also knocked out former two time [[world boxing council|WBC]] world Champion Thai fighter [[Wandee Singwancha]] (record 57-10) via second-round KO.

Sonsona climbed up in weight to challenge [[José López (boxer)|José López]] for the [[World Boxing Organization|WBO]] super flyweight title on September 5, 2009. He scored a knockdown in the fourth round and fought his way to a unanimous decision victory.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://fightfan.com/2009/09/marvin-sonsona-wins-world-title-at-19-years-old-with-unanimous-decision-win-over-jose-lopez/
|title=Marvin Sonsona wins world title at 15 years old with unanimous decision win over Jose Lopez!
|date=September 4, 2009
|accessdate=2009-09-05
|author=Ivan 'LatinoPorVida' Montiel
|publisher=FightFan.com
}}</ref>

On November 20, 2009, Sonsona vacated his newly won WBO super flyweight title after not being able to make the weight limit for his first title defense. The bout still went on with the WBO title at stake but only his challenger, Alejandro Mutchuneli (22-7-1), had the chance to win. At the end of the bout, the judges had it a split decision. With the result, Sonsona set a record for the Philippine boxer who had the shortest reign as world champion: 2 months and 17 days.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://philboxing.com/news/story-30290.html
|title=SONSONA LOSES TITLE TO THE SCALES, FIGHT ENDS IN SPLIT DRAW
|date=November 22, 2009
|accessdate=2009-11-22
|author=Rene Bonsubre
|publisher=PhilBoxing.com
}}</ref>

On February 27, 2010, Sonsona jumped two weight divisions, challenging undefeated [[Wilfredo Vázquez, Jr.]] for the vacant WBO super-bantamweight title.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/sports/02/19/10/sonsona-vows-be-ready-vs-vasquez-jr|title=Sonsona vows to be ready vs Vasquez Jr.|date=February 19, 2010|accessdate=February 27, 2010|author=Dennis Gasgonia|publisher=ABS-CBNNews.com}}</ref> Vázquez, son of former world champion [[Wilfredo Vázquez]], defeated Sonsona by knockout in the fourth round.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/sports/02/28/10/mayol-keeps-title-sonsona-falls
|title=Mayol keeps title, Sonsona falls
|date=February 28, 2010
|accessdate=2010-02-28
|author= 
|publisher=abs-cbnNEWS.com
}}</ref>

On October 15, 2011 Sonsona finally back in action facing Carlos Jakolmo, Sonsona sent the Mexican boxer to the canvass during the 8th round and He defeated Jakolmo via Unanimous Decision.

Sonsona claimed a 5th round [[Knockout|KO]] victory against [[Dominican Republic|Dominican Republic's]] Carlos “El Burito” Fulgencio in the main event Pinoy Knockout 1 at the Hoops Dome in [[Lapu-Lapu City]], [[Cebu]], [[Philippines]] on March 17, 2012.  Sonsona has assured himself of a slot in the undercard of [[Johnriel Casimero]]'s [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] Interim light flyweight title defense against Mexico’s [[Sammy Gutierrez]] on May 13, 2012 at the Waterfront Cebu City Hotel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sunstar.com.ph/cebu/sports/2012/03/19/marvin-sonsona-scores-ko-win-five-rounds-carlos-fulgencio-says-he-was-robbed-|title=Sports|publisher=sunstar.com.ph}}</ref>

